First paste the following script tag into your Custom HTML: 

<script src="https://static.cargo.site/scripts/loader.js" data-name="eyeroll"></script>

Then add your eye images to a page, select one of them, click the Image Options button in the Formatting Toolbar, and type #eye in the Caption field. Do the same with the other eye.


To change the speed and range of rotatation, add the range and/or rollspeed  attributes:

#eye range:0.8
#eye rollspeed:0.4 

These values can be a decimal from 0 – 1.

You can also add #eye to non-image elements by adding a “data-caption” via Code View:<h2 data-caption="#eye rollspeed:0.4">This element will rotate towards the cursor</h2>
